USE CASE: 2 Generate report on cities
CHARACTERISTIC INFORMATION,
Goal in Context,
As a User I want to produce a report on the populations of cities in a (world/continent/region/country/district) organised by largest to smallest.
World Database
Level,
Primary task
Preconditions,
Database contains population and location data for cities.
Success End Condition,
Generated a report on the populations of cities in a (world/continent/region/country/district) organised by largest to smallest.
Failed End Condition,
No report is produced
Primary Actor,
Report user
Trigger,
A request for cities in (world/continent/region/country/district) to be ranked by population
MAIN SUCCESS SCENARIO,
The Report user requests a list of cities organised by population.,
The user selects the scope:,
World,
Continent,
Region,
District,
Population,
The system retrieves all city records that match the selected scope.,
Report contains the required columns: Name, Country, District, Population.,
Report User provides report to the organisation.,
EXTENSIONS,
Invalid scope selected
,
If the user does not select a valid scope (World, Continent, Region, Country or District), the system prompts the user to choose one before continuing.,
If the user enters a district region name that does not exist in the database, the system displays a message such as “No such district/region found” and does not run the report.,
No City records returned
,
If no city records are returned from the report users' query, the system shows an error message.,
SUB-VARIATIONS,
If two cities have the same population, the system applies a secondary alphabetical sort by city name.,
SCHEDULE,
DUE DATE: 12/11/25
